        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>salted paper processes [300053495], photographic processes [300133268], photography and photographic processes and techniques [300149146], image-making processes and techniques [300053159], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a number of closely related variants of the salted paper process in which the paper was made translucent by waxing before sensitizing. Do not use if a paper negative has been waxed after processing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para diferentes variantes estrechamente relacionadas al proceso en papel de sal, en las cuales el papel se ha hecho translúcido aplicando cera antes de sensibilizarlo. No usar si un negativo de papel ha sido encerado después del procesamiento.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een aantal nauw verwante varianten van het zoutpapierprocédé waarbij het papier lichtdoorlatend wordt gemaakt door het met was te bestrijken alvorens het lichtgelig te maken. Niet te gebruiken wanneer een papiernegatief met was wordt behandeld na belichting.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>泛指數種相似的銀鹽紙法，在感光之前先將紙基上蠟，讓紙基呈半透明狀。如果在沖印過程中，紙質負片是經過感光處理之後才上蠟，就不能以此詞彙指稱。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
